## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="49a76-170">O vínculo entre o ActiveX Data Objects (ADO) e o ADO.NET é uma operação unidirecional em que você pode copiar dados do ADO para o <xref:System.Data.DataSet>, mas todas as atualizações para os dados devem ser tratadas pelo ADO.NET.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="49a76-170">The link between ActiveX Data Objects (ADO) and ADO.NET is a one-way operation in that you can copy data from ADO to the <xref:System.Data.DataSet>, but any updates to the data must be handled by ADO.NET.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="49a76-171">Esta sobrecarga do <xref:System.Data.OleDb.OleDbDataAdapter.Fill%2A> método não fecha a entrada `Recordset` na conclusão do <xref:System.Data.OleDb.OleDbDataAdapter.Fill%2A> operação.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="49a76-171">This overload of the <xref:System.Data.OleDb.OleDbDataAdapter.Fill%2A> method does not close the input `Recordset` on completion of the <xref:System.Data.OleDb.OleDbDataAdapter.Fill%2A> operation.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="49a76-172">Ao lidar com instruções SQL em lotes que retornem vários resultados, essa implementação de <xref:System.Data.OleDb.OleDbDataAdapter.Fill%2A> e <xref:System.Data.Common.DbDataAdapter.FillSchema%2A> para o DB.NET Framework provedor de dados recupera informações de esquema para apenas o primeiro resultado.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="49a76-172">When handling batch SQL statements that return multiple results, this implementation of <xref:System.Data.OleDb.OleDbDataAdapter.Fill%2A> and <xref:System.Data.Common.DbDataAdapter.FillSchema%2A> for the OLE DB.NET Framework Data Provider retrieves schema information for only the first result.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="49a76-173">O <xref:System.Data.OleDb.OleDbDataAdapter.Fill%2A> operação adiciona as linhas para o destino especificado <xref:System.Data.DataTable> objeto o <xref:System.Data.DataSet>, criando o <xref:System.Data.DataTable> objeto se ele ainda não existir.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="49a76-173">The <xref:System.Data.OleDb.OleDbDataAdapter.Fill%2A> operation adds the rows to the specified destination <xref:System.Data.DataTable> object in the <xref:System.Data.DataSet>, creating the <xref:System.Data.DataTable> object if it does not already exist.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="49a76-174">Quando você cria um <xref:System.Data.DataTable> objeto, o <xref:System.Data.OleDb.OleDbDataAdapter.Fill%2A> operação normalmente cria apenas os metadados de nome de coluna.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="49a76-174">When you create a <xref:System.Data.DataTable> object, the <xref:System.Data.OleDb.OleDbDataAdapter.Fill%2A> operation ordinarily creates only column name metadata.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="49a76-175">No entanto, caso a propriedade <xref:System.Data.Common.DataAdapter.MissingSchemaAction%2A> seja definida como `AddWithKey`, as chaves primárias apropriadas e as restrições também são criadas.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="49a76-175">However, if the <xref:System.Data.Common.DataAdapter.MissingSchemaAction%2A> property is set to `AddWithKey`, appropriate primary keys and constraints are also created.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="49a76-176">Você pode usar o <xref:System.Data.OleDb.OleDbDataAdapter.Fill%2A> método várias vezes no mesmo <xref:System.Data.DataTable>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="49a76-176">You can use the <xref:System.Data.OleDb.OleDbDataAdapter.Fill%2A> method multiple times on the same <xref:System.Data.DataTable>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="49a76-177">Caso haja uma chave primária, as linhas de entrada são mescladas com linhas correspondentes já existentes.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="49a76-177">If a primary key exists, incoming rows are merged with matching rows that already exist.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="49a76-178">Caso não haja nenhuma chave primária, as linhas de entrada são acrescentadas ao <xref:System.Data.DataTable>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="49a76-178">If no primary key exists, incoming rows are appended to the <xref:System.Data.DataTable>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="49a76-179">Se houver informações de chave primária, linhas duplicadas são reconciliadas e aparecer apenas uma vez no <xref:System.Data.DataTable> que corresponde do <xref:System.Data.DataSet>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="49a76-179">If primary key information is present, any duplicate rows are reconciled and only appear one time in the <xref:System.Data.DataTable> that corresponds to the <xref:System.Data.DataSet>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="49a76-180">Informações de chave primária podem ser definidas por meio de <xref:System.Data.Common.DbDataAdapter.FillSchema%2A>, especificando o <xref:System.Data.DataTable.PrimaryKey%2A> propriedade do <xref:System.Data.DataTable>, ou definindo o <xref:System.Data.Common.DataAdapter.MissingSchemaAction%2A> propriedade `AddWithKey`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="49a76-180">Primary key information may be set either through <xref:System.Data.Common.DbDataAdapter.FillSchema%2A>, by specifying the <xref:System.Data.DataTable.PrimaryKey%2A> property of the <xref:System.Data.DataTable>, or by setting the <xref:System.Data.Common.DataAdapter.MissingSchemaAction%2A> property to `AddWithKey`.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="49a76-181">Se o <xref:System.Data.OleDb.OleDbDataAdapter.SelectCommand%2A> retornar os resultados de um OUTER JOIN, o `DataAdapter` não definirá um valor de <xref:System.Data.DataTable.PrimaryKey%2A> para o<xref:System.Data.DataTable> resultante.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="49a76-181">If the <xref:System.Data.OleDb.OleDbDataAdapter.SelectCommand%2A> returns the results of an OUTER JOIN, the `DataAdapter` does not set a <xref:System.Data.DataTable.PrimaryKey%2A> value for the resulting <xref:System.Data.DataTable>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="49a76-182">Você deve definir explicitamente a chave primária para certificar-se de que as linhas duplicadas são resolvidas corretamente.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="49a76-182">You must explicitly define the primary key to make sure that duplicate rows are resolved correctly.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="49a76-183">Para obter mais informações, consulte [definindo chaves primárias](~/docs/framework/data/adonet/dataset-datatable-dataview/defining-primary-keys.md).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="49a76-183">For more information, see [Defining Primary Keys](~/docs/framework/data/adonet/dataset-datatable-dataview/defining-primary-keys.md).</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="49a76-184">Para funcionar corretamente com o provedor de dados .NET Framework para OLE DB, `AddWithKey` requer que o provedor OLE DB nativo obtém informações necessárias de chave primárias definindo a propriedade DBPROP_UNIQUEROWS e, em seguida, determina quais colunas são primárias colunas de chave examinando DBCOLUMN_KEYCOLUMN no `IColumnsRowset`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="49a76-184">To function correctly with the .NET Framework Data Provider for OLE DB, `AddWithKey` requires that the native OLE DB provider obtains required primary key information by setting the DBPROP_UNIQUEROWS property, and then determines which columns are primary key columns by examining DBCOLUMN_KEYCOLUMN in the `IColumnsRowset`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="49a76-185">Como alternativa o usuário pode definir explicitamente as restrições de chave primárias em cada <xref:System.Data.DataTable>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="49a76-185">Alternatively the user may explicitly set the primary key constraints on each <xref:System.Data.DataTable>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="49a76-186">Isso garante que os registros de entrada que corresponde aos registros existentes são atualizados em vez de acrescentado.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="49a76-186">This makes sure that incoming records that match existing records are updated instead of appended.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="49a76-187">Se o <xref:System.Data.OleDb.OleDbDataAdapter> encontra colunas duplicadas ao preencher um <xref:System.Data.DataTable>, ele gera nomes para as colunas subsequentes, usando o padrão "*columnname*1", "*columnname*2","*columnname*3", e assim por diante.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="49a76-187">If the <xref:System.Data.OleDb.OleDbDataAdapter> encounters duplicate columns while populating a <xref:System.Data.DataTable>, it generates names for the subsequent columns, using the pattern "*columnname*1", "*columnname*2", "*columnname*3", and so on.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="49a76-188">Nomes de coluna vazia são adicionados para o <xref:System.Data.DataTable>, usando uma cadeia de caracteres vazia para a primeira coluna, seguido por "1", "2", "3" e assim por diante para as colunas vazias subsequentes.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="49a76-188">Empty column names are added to the <xref:System.Data.DataTable>, using an empty string for the first column, followed by "1", "2", "3", and so on for the subsequent empty columns.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="49a76-189">Os valores no ADO `Recordset` ou `Record` objetos são convertidos em comum idioma tipos de tempo de execução para o armazenamento no <xref:System.Data.DataSet>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="49a76-189">Values in ADO `Recordset` or `Record` objects are converted to common language runtime types for storage in the <xref:System.Data.DataSet>.</span></span>  
  
> [!CAUTION]
>  <span data-ttu-id="49a76-190">Esta sobrecarga do <xref:System.Data.OleDb.OleDbDataAdapter.Fill%2A> não implicitamente chamada do método `Close` no objeto ADO quando a operação de preenchimento é concluída.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="49a76-190">This overload of the <xref:System.Data.OleDb.OleDbDataAdapter.Fill%2A> method does not implicitly call `Close` on the ADO object when the fill operation is complete.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="49a76-191">Portanto, sempre chamar `Close` quando terminar de usar o ADO `Recordset` ou `Record` objetos.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="49a76-191">Therefore, always call `Close` when you are finished using ADO `Recordset` or `Record` objects.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="49a76-192">Isso torna-se de que a conexão subjacente para uma fonte de dados é liberado de maneira oportuna e também impede violações de acesso possíveis devido a objetos não gerenciados do ADO que está sendo recuperados pela coleta de lixo quando as referências existentes ainda existem.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="49a76-192">This makes sure that the underlying connection to a data source is released in a timely manner, and also prevents possible access violations because of unmanaged ADO objects being reclaimed by garbage collection when existing references still exist.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="49a76-193">Quando você chama o `TableMappings.Add` método em um `DataAdapter` e você mapear explicitamente o parâmetro da tabela de origem para uma cadeia de caracteres vazia, o conjunto de dados é preenchido com êxito usando a tabela de origem, mas o conjunto de dados será preenchido com nada.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="49a76-193">When you call the `TableMappings.Add` method on a `DataAdapter` and you explicitly map the source table parameter to an empty string, the dataset is successfully filled using the source table, but the dataset will be populated with nothing.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="49a76-194">Por exemplo, no exemplo a seguir, `rDataSet` será preenchida com nada.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="49a76-194">For example, in the following example, `rDataSet` will be populated with nothing.</span></span>  
  
```  
rAdapter.TableMappings.Add("source table", "");  
rAdapter.Fill(rDataSet, "source table");     
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="49a76-195">Este exemplo mostra como você pode ignorar um resultado ao lidar com vários resultados.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="49a76-195">This example shows how you can skip a result when dealing with multiple results.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="49a76-196">O exemplo a seguir usa uma <xref:System.Data.OleDb.OleDbDataAdapter> para preencher um <xref:System.Data.DataTable> usando ADO `Recordset`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="49a76-196">The following example uses an <xref:System.Data.OleDb.OleDbDataAdapter> to fill a <xref:System.Data.DataTable> using an ADO `Recordset`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="49a76-197">Este exemplo supõe que você tenha criado um ADO `Recordset`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="49a76-197">This example assumes that you have created an ADO `Recordset`.</span></span>  
  
```vb  
Dim custDA As OleDbDataAdapter = New OleDbDataAdapter()  
     Dim custDS As DataSet = New DataSet  
     Dim custTable As DataTable = New DataTable("Customers")  
     custTable.Columns.Add("CustomerID", Type.GetType("System.String"))  
     custTable.Columns.Add("CompanyName", Type.GetType("System.String"))  
     custDS.Tables.Add(custTable)  
     'Use ADO objects from ADO library (msado15.dll) imported  
     ' as.NET library ADODB.dll using TlbImp.exe  
     Dim adoConn As ADODB.Connection = New ADODB.Connection()  
     Dim adoRS As ADODB.Recordset = New ADODB.Recordset()  
     adoConn.Open("Provider=SQLOLEDB;Data Source=localhost;Initial Catalog=Northwind;Integrated Security=SSPI;", "", "", -1)  
     adoRS.Open("SELECT CustomerID, CompanyName FROM Customers", adoConn, ADODB.CursorTypeEnum.adOpenForwardOnly, ADODB.LockTypeEnum.adLockReadOnly, 1)  
     custDA.Fill(custTable, adoRS)  
     adoRS.Close()  
     adoConn.Close()  
```  
  
```csharp  
OleDbDataAdapter custDA = new OleDbDataAdapter();  
     DataSet custDS = new DataSet();  
     DataTable custTable = new DataTable("Customers");  
     custTable.Columns.Add("CustomerID", typeof(String));  
     custTable.Columns.Add("CompanyName", typeof(String));  
     custDS.Tables.Add(custTable);  
     //Use ADO objects from ADO library (msado15.dll) imported  
     //  as.NET library ADODB.dll using TlbImp.exe  
     ADODB.Connection adoConn = new ADODB.Connection();  
     ADODB.Recordset adoRS = new ADODB.Recordset();  
     adoConn.Open("Provider=SQLOLEDB;Data Source=localhost;Initial Catalog=Northwind;Integrated Security=SSPI;", "", "", -1);  
     adoRS.Open("SELECT CustomerID, CompanyName FROM Customers", adoConn, ADODB.CursorTypeEnum.adOpenForwardOnly, ADODB.LockTypeEnum.adLockReadOnly, 1);  
     custDA.Fill(custTable, adoRS);  
     adoRS.Close();  
     adoConn.Close();  
```
